body:
@XiaoJiNu did you modify the repo? What's your operating system?

On Linux and MacOS detect.py works fine with no changes. If you run this code you should get zero erors or warnings:

```
git clone https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3
cd yolov3
python3 detect.py
```
@glenn-jocher ，on windows 10 is ok, but on ubuntu, unless I create __init__.py，it would output error, I don't konw why

@XiaoJiNu Is your folder and file structure the same as in this repository?
Are you used Python3?
@Lepiloff I use python 3.7.2 and I didn't change folder file structure, Anyway, I'm training correctly now ^_^

@XiaoJiNu that's strange. Maybe you have a folder with the identical name listed in your path somewhere?

I've been running on GCP VMs with Debian 9 (https://cloud.google.com/deep-learning-vm/), on my MacBook Pro with MacOS, and with Windows using Parallels on my MacBook Pro with no issues.
I think you may have installed utils package. ("sudo pip3 install utils")

File "/home/yolov3/models.py", line 5, in <module>
    from utils.parse_config import *
ImportError: No module named utils.parse_config
I am getting errors although installed 
conda install python-utils
conda install configparser
@leonzfa @husnejahan utils refers to the folder in this repo, it does not require any package installation.

@XiaoJiNu I had the same issue, when I run python detect.py, the same error happen, the information show below:

(yolo) pisey@pc:~/anaconda3/envs/yolo/yolov3$ python detect.py 
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "detect.py", line 5, in <module>
    from models import *
  File "/home/pisey/anaconda3/envs/yolo/yolov3/models.py", line 1, in <module>
    from utils.parse_config import *
ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'utils.parse_config'

after I follow your sug, make the new file, the "init.py", the same error happen, anything else you did? any other file need editor?
I run in ubuntu 16.04.
